Aim of the aid :
The individual aid will be granted for investment in a livestock breeding centre with a view to maintaining protection standards for the natural environment and to improving hygiene conditions and livestock welfare. The investment will be used to remove dangerous roofing containing asbestos and to replace it with new roofing free of that substance.
This work is primarily required because of the decision of the Namysłowski District Buildings Inspector of 2 July 2004 ordering %quot%FERMA-POL%quot% in Zalesie to remove materials containing asbestos from its premises. The decision stated that damage to asbestine tiles could result in the release of asbestos fibres into the atmosphere, so causing a threat to human health and the environment, including domestic livestock in this case.
Exposure to asbestos carries with it the risk of diseases affecting the respiratory system such as asbestosis, lung cancer, pleural lesions, etc.; this has been borne out by experiments conducted since the 1970s. In 1977 European Community experts drew up a report on the risk to public health caused by environmental exposure to asbestos dust, confirming its pathogenic effect.
The investment moreover falls within the Programme to remove asbestos and products containing asbestos used on Polish terrority, adopted by the Polish Council of Ministers on 14 May 2002, one of whose aims is to rid Poland of asbestos and the products containing it that have been in use for many years now.
